## 12-Factor Agents (Dex Horthy, 2024)
direction: down

intro: {
  shape: text
  label: "The '12-Factor App' for LLM-powered software.\nProduction LLM apps are CONVENTIONAL software with a probabilistic core.\nLessons from years of agent building, distilled to 12 factors."
  style.italic: true
  style.font-color: "#7c3aed"
}

control: {
  label: "CONTROL FACTORS (you own these)"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#bbf7d0"
  style.stroke: "#16a34a"
  body: {label: "1. Natural language -> tool calls\n2. Own your prompts\n3. Own your context window\n4. Tools are just structured outputs\n5. Unify execution + business state\n6. Launch / pause / resume with simple APIs"; shape: text}
}

design: {
  label: "DESIGN FACTORS (architectural choices)"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#dbeafe"
  style.stroke: "#2563eb"
  body: {label: "7. Contact humans with tool calls\n8. Own your control flow\n9. Compact errors into context\n10. Small focused agents\n11. Trigger from anywhere, meet users where they are\n12. Make your agent a stateless reducer"; shape: text}
}

bigidea: {
  label: "Big idea"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#fde68a"
  style.stroke: "#d97706"
  body: {label: "Most agent frameworks abstract too much.\nYou end up fighting the framework when you need control.\n\nThe 12 factors: own the pieces that matter (prompts, context,\ncontrol flow, error handling). Use frameworks for plumbing,\nnot for the agent's brain."; shape: text}
}

intro -> control
intro -> design
control -> bigidea
design -> bigidea
